78/***
79 *** Supported DLZ DB Implementations Registry
80 ***/
81
82static ISC_LIST(dns_dlzimplementation_t) dlz_implementations;
83static isc_rwlock_t dlz_implock;
84static isc_once_t once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;
85
86static void
87dlz_initialize(void) {
88 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_rwlock_init(&dlz_implock, 0, 0) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
89 ISC_LIST_INIT(dlz_implementations);
90}
91
92/*%
93 * Searches the dlz_implementations list for a driver matching name.
94 */
95static inline dns_dlzimplementation_t *
96dlz_impfind(const char *name) {
97 dns_dlzimplementation_t *imp;
98
99 for (imp = ISC_LIST_HEAD(dlz_implementations);
100 imp != NULL;
101 imp = ISC_LIST_NEXT(imp, link))
102 if (strcasecmp(name, imp->name) == 0)
103 return (imp);
104 return (NULL);
105}

107/***
108 *** Basic DLZ Methods
109 ***/
110
111isc_result_t
112dns_dlzallowzonexfr(dns_view_t *view, const dns_name_t *name,
113 const isc_sockaddr_t *clientaddr, dns_db_t **dbp)
114{
115 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
116 dns_dlzallowzonexfr_t allowzonexfr;
117 dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdb;
118
119 /*
120 * Performs checks to make sure data is as we expect it to be.
121 */
122 REQUIRE(name != NULL);
123 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && *dbp == NULL);
124
125 /*
126 * Find a driver in which the zone exists and transfer is supported
127 */
128 for (dlzdb = ISC_LIST_HEAD(view->dlz_searched);
129 dlzdb != NULL;
130 dlzdb = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dlzdb, link))
131 {
132 REQUIRE(DNS_DLZ_VALID(dlzdb));
133
134 allowzonexfr = dlzdb->implementation->methods->allowzonexfr;
135 result = (*allowzonexfr)(dlzdb->implementation->driverarg,
136 dlzdb->dbdata, dlzdb->mctx,
137 view->rdclass, name, clientaddr, dbp);
138
139 /*
140 * if ISC_R_NOPERM, we found the right database but
141 * the zone may not transfer.
142 */
143 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == ISC_R_NOPERM)
144 return (result);
145 }
146
147 if (result == ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED)
148 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
149
150 return (result);
151}
152
153isc_result_t
154dns_dlzcreate(isc_mem_t *mctx, const char *dlzname, const char *drivername,
155 unsigned int argc, char *argv[], dns_dlzdb_t **dbp)
156{
157 dns_dlzimplementation_t *impinfo;
158 isc_result_t result;
159 dns_dlzdb_t *db = NULL;
160
161 /*
162 * initialize the dlz_implementations list, this is guaranteed
163 * to only really happen once.
164 */
165 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, dlz_initialize) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
166
167 /*
168 * Performs checks to make sure data is as we expect it to be.
169 */
170 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && *dbp == NULL);
171 REQUIRE(dlzname != NULL);
172 REQUIRE(drivername != NULL);
173 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
174
175 /* write log message */
176 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
177 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_INFO,
178 "Loading '%s' using driver %s", dlzname, drivername);
179
180 /* lock the dlz_implementations list so we can search it. */
181 RWLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
182
183 /* search for the driver implementation */
184 impinfo = dlz_impfind(drivername);
185 if (impinfo == NULL) {
186 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
187
188 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
189 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
190 "unsupported DLZ database driver '%s'."
191 " %s not loaded.",
192 drivername, dlzname);
193
194 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
195 }
196
197 /* Allocate memory to hold the DLZ database driver */
198 db = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dlzdb_t));
199 if (db == NULL) {
200 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
201 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
202 }
203
204 /* Make sure memory region is set to all 0's */
205 memset(db, 0, sizeof(dns_dlzdb_t));
206
207 ISC_LINK_INIT(db, link);
208 db->implementation = impinfo;
209 if (dlzname != NULL)
210 db->dlzname = isc_mem_strdup(mctx, dlzname);
211
212 /* Create a new database using implementation 'drivername'. */
213 result = ((impinfo->methods->create)(mctx, dlzname, argc, argv,
214 impinfo->driverarg,
215 &db->dbdata));
216
217 /* mark the DLZ driver as valid */
218 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
219 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
220 db->magic = DNS_DLZ_MAGIC;
221 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &db->mctx);
222 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
223 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2),
224 "DLZ driver loaded successfully.");
225 *dbp = db;
226 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
227 } else {
228 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
229 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
230 "DLZ driver failed to load.");
231 }
232
233 /* impinfo->methods->create failed. */
234 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_read);
235 isc_mem_put(mctx, db, sizeof(dns_dlzdb_t));
236 return (result);
237}
238
239void
240dns_dlzdestroy(dns_dlzdb_t **dbp) {
241 dns_dlzdestroy_t destroy;
242 dns_dlzdb_t *db;
243
244 /* Write debugging message to log */
245 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
246 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2),
247 "Unloading DLZ driver.");
248
249 /*
250 * Perform checks to make sure data is as we expect it to be.
251 */
252 REQUIRE(dbp != NULL && DNS_DLZ_VALID(*dbp));
253
254 db = *dbp;
255 *dbp = NULL;
256
257 if (db->ssutable != NULL)
258 dns_ssutable_detach(&db->ssutable);
259
260 /* call the drivers destroy method */
261 if (db->dlzname != NULL)
262 isc_mem_free(db->mctx, db->dlzname);
263 destroy = db->implementation->methods->destroy;
264 (*destroy)(db->implementation->driverarg, db->dbdata);
265 /* return memory and detach */
266 isc_mem_putanddetach(&db->mctx, db, sizeof(dns_dlzdb_t));
267}

269/*%
270 * Registers a DLZ driver. This basically just adds the dlz
271 * driver to the list of available drivers in the dlz_implementations list.
272 */
273isc_result_t
274dns_dlzregister(const char *drivername, const dns_dlzmethods_t *methods,
275 void *driverarg, isc_mem_t *mctx,
276 dns_dlzimplementation_t **dlzimp)
277{
278
279 dns_dlzimplementation_t *dlz_imp;
280
281 /* Write debugging message to log */
282 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
283 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2),
284 "Registering DLZ driver '%s'", drivername);
285
286 /*
287 * Performs checks to make sure data is as we expect it to be.
288 */
289 REQUIRE(drivername != NULL);
290 REQUIRE(methods != NULL);
291 REQUIRE(methods->create != NULL);
292 REQUIRE(methods->destroy != NULL);
293 REQUIRE(methods->findzone != NULL);
294 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
295 REQUIRE(dlzimp != NULL && *dlzimp == NULL);
296
297 /*
298 * initialize the dlz_implementations list, this is guaranteed
299 * to only really happen once.
300 */
301 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, dlz_initialize) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
302
303 /* lock the dlz_implementations list so we can modify it. */
304 RWLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
305
306 /*
307 * check that another already registered driver isn't using
308 * the same name
309 */
310 dlz_imp = dlz_impfind(drivername);
311 if (dlz_imp != NULL) {
312 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
313 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2),
314 "DLZ Driver '%s' already registered",
315 drivername);
316 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
317 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
318 }
319
320 /*
321 * Allocate memory for a dlz_implementation object. Error if
322 * we cannot.
323 */
324 dlz_imp = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_dlzimplementation_t));
325 if (dlz_imp == NULL) {
326 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
327 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
328 }
329
330 /* Make sure memory region is set to all 0's */
331 memset(dlz_imp, 0, sizeof(dns_dlzimplementation_t));
332
333 /* Store the data passed into this method */
334 dlz_imp->name = drivername;
335 dlz_imp->methods = methods;
336 dlz_imp->mctx = NULL;
337 dlz_imp->driverarg = driverarg;
338
339 /* attach the new dlz_implementation object to a memory context */
340 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &dlz_imp->mctx);
341
342 /*
343 * prepare the dlz_implementation object to be put in a list,
344 * and append it to the list
345 */
346 ISC_LINK_INIT(dlz_imp, link);
347 ISC_LIST_APPEND(dlz_implementations, dlz_imp, link);
348
349 /* Unlock the dlz_implementations list. */
350 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
351
352 /* Pass back the dlz_implementation that we created. */
353 *dlzimp = dlz_imp;
354
355 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
356}
357
358/*%
359 * Tokenize the string "s" into whitespace-separated words,
360 * return the number of words in '*argcp' and an array
361 * of pointers to the words in '*argvp'. The caller
362 * must free the array using isc_mem_put(). The string
363 * is modified in-place.
364 */
365isc_result_t
366dns_dlzstrtoargv(isc_mem_t *mctx, char *s,
367 unsigned int *argcp, char ***argvp)
368{
369 return(isc_commandline_strtoargv(mctx, s, argcp, argvp, 0));
370}

372/*%
373 * Unregisters a DLZ driver. This basically just removes the dlz
374 * driver from the list of available drivers in the dlz_implementations list.
375 */
376void
377dns_dlzunregister(dns_dlzimplementation_t **dlzimp) {
378 dns_dlzimplementation_t *dlz_imp;
379 isc_mem_t *mctx;
380
381 /* Write debugging message to log */
382 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
383 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(2),
384 "Unregistering DLZ driver.");
385
386 /*
387 * Performs checks to make sure data is as we expect it to be.
388 */
389 REQUIRE(dlzimp != NULL && *dlzimp != NULL);
390
391 /*
392 * initialize the dlz_implementations list, this is guaranteed
393 * to only really happen once.
394 */
395 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, dlz_initialize) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
396
397 dlz_imp = *dlzimp;
398
399 /* lock the dlz_implementations list so we can modify it. */
400 RWLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
401
402 /* remove the dlz_implementation object from the list */
403 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(dlz_implementations, dlz_imp, link);
404 mctx = dlz_imp->mctx;
405
406 /*
407 * Return the memory back to the available memory pool and
408 * remove it from the memory context.
409 */
410 isc_mem_put(mctx, dlz_imp, sizeof(dns_dlzimplementation_t));
411 isc_mem_detach(&mctx);
412
413 /* Unlock the dlz_implementations list. */
414 RWUNLOCK(&dlz_implock, isc_rwlocktype_write);
415}

417/*
418 * Create a writeable DLZ zone. This can be called by DLZ drivers
419 * during configure() to create a zone that can be updated. The zone
420 * type is set to dns_zone_dlz, which is equivalent to a master zone
421 *
422 * This function uses a callback setup in dns_dlzconfigure() to call
423 * into the server zone code to setup the remaining pieces of server
424 * specific functionality on the zone
425 */
426isc_result_t
427dns_dlz_writeablezone(dns_view_t *view, dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdb,
428 const char *zone_name)
429{
430 dns_zone_t *zone = NULL;
431 dns_zone_t *dupzone = NULL;
432 isc_result_t result;
433 isc_buffer_t buffer;
434 dns_fixedname_t fixorigin;
435 dns_name_t *origin;
436
437 REQUIRE(DNS_DLZ_VALID(dlzdb));
438
439 REQUIRE(dlzdb->configure_callback != NULL);
440
441 isc_buffer_constinit(&buffer, zone_name, strlen(zone_name));
442 isc_buffer_add(&buffer, strlen(zone_name));
443 dns_fixedname_init(&fixorigin);
444 result = dns_name_fromtext(dns_fixedname_name(&fixorigin),
445 &buffer, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
446 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
447 goto cleanup;
448 origin = dns_fixedname_name(&fixorigin);
449
450 if (!dlzdb->search) {
451 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
452 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
453 "DLZ %s has 'search no;', but attempted to "
454 "register writeable zone %s.",
455 dlzdb->dlzname, zone_name);
456 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
457 goto cleanup;
458 }
459
460 /* See if the zone already exists */
461 result = dns_view_findzone(view, origin, &dupzone);
462 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
463 dns_zone_detach(&dupzone);
464 result = ISC_R_EXISTS;
465 goto cleanup;
466 }
467 INSIST(dupzone == NULL);
468
469 /* Create it */
470 result = dns_zone_create(&zone, view->mctx);
471 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
472 goto cleanup;
473 result = dns_zone_setorigin(zone, origin);
474 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
475 goto cleanup;
476 dns_zone_setview(zone, view);
477
478 dns_zone_setadded(zone, true);
479
480 if (dlzdb->ssutable == NULL) {
481 result = dns_ssutable_createdlz(dlzdb->mctx,
482 &dlzdb->ssutable, dlzdb);
483 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
484 goto cleanup;
485 }
486 dns_zone_setssutable(zone, dlzdb->ssutable);
487
488 result = dlzdb->configure_callback(view, dlzdb, zone);
489 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
490 goto cleanup;
491
492 result = dns_view_addzone(view, zone);
493
494
495 cleanup:
496 if (zone != NULL)
497 dns_zone_detach(&zone);
498
499 return (result);
500}
501
502/*%
503 * Configure a DLZ driver. This is optional, and if supplied gives
504 * the backend an opportunity to configure parameters related to DLZ.
505 */
506isc_result_t
507dns_dlzconfigure(dns_view_t *view, dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdb,
508 dlzconfigure_callback_t callback)
509{
510 dns_dlzimplementation_t *impl;
511 isc_result_t result;
512
513 REQUIRE(DNS_DLZ_VALID(dlzdb));
514 REQUIRE(dlzdb->implementation != NULL);
515
516 impl = dlzdb->implementation;
517
518 if (impl->methods->configure == NULL)
519 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
520
521 dlzdb->configure_callback = callback;
522
523 result = impl->methods->configure(impl->driverarg, dlzdb->dbdata,
524 view, dlzdb);
525 return (result);
526}
527
528bool
529dns_dlz_ssumatch(dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdatabase, const dns_name_t *signer,
530 const dns_name_t *name, const isc_netaddr_t *tcpaddr,
531 dns_rdatatype_t type, const dst_key_t *key)
532{
533 dns_dlzimplementation_t *impl;
534 bool r;
535
536 REQUIRE(dlzdatabase != NULL);
537 REQUIRE(dlzdatabase->implementation != NULL);
538 REQUIRE(dlzdatabase->implementation->methods != NULL);
539 impl = dlzdatabase->implementation;
540
541 if (impl->methods->ssumatch == NULL) {
542 isc_log_write(dns_lctx, DNS_LOGCATEGORY_DATABASE,
543 DNS_LOGMODULE_DLZ, ISC_LOG_INFO,
544 "No ssumatch method for DLZ database");
545 return (false);
546 }
547
548 r = impl->methods->ssumatch(signer, name, tcpaddr, type, key,
549 impl->driverarg, dlzdatabase->dbdata);
550 return (r);
551}
